 path in csv_paths:\n    df = prepare_beach_datasheet(path)\n    failed = df[df['Enterococcus'] > 104]\n    rain_failed += int((failed['1-Day Rain'] > 0).sum())\n    total_failed += int(len(failed))\n\npercentage = (rain_failed / total_failed * 100) if total_failed else 0.0\nprint(f'{percentage:.2f}')", "reason": "Rewrote the code to correctly parse the downloaded beach datasheet CSVs with their two-row headers, reshape each file into tidy sample rows, count failed Enterococcus samples (>104), count how many of those had 1-Day Rain > 0, aggregate across all downloaded CSVs, and print the final percentage only."}) [toolUseId=call_hXVXd2H5qSxXjwVSDqqGAscF]
